<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_cʼæǧæʒ" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
    <form type="lemma"><orth>cʼæǧæʒ</orth></form>
    <sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>челнок в ткацком станке</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>loom shuttle</q>
            </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>шпулька швейной машины</q>
            </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>bobbin of sewing machine</q>
            </cit></sense></sense>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Несомненная связь с <mentioned xml:lang=""
                    ><lang/><w>čʼäǧišk</w><gloss><q>задвижка</q></gloss></mentioned> и возможная с
            <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>səǧəs</w><gloss><q>клин</q></gloss></mentioned>
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>IV 620</biblScope></bibl>). Если
        допустить, что в исходной среде существовал перебой %iǧ%i || %iv%i (ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_cigon"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ciwan"/> ‘чугун’, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_suǧaq"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sovaq"/> ‘сайгак’ и др.), то мы
        можем восстановить параллельную форму *%icavac%i, которая окажется весьма близкой к
            <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><w>цывца</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><w>цевка</w><gloss><q>шпулька</q></gloss></mentioned>, . К осетинскому
        %icʼæǧæʒ%i примыкает <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">()
                </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">()
                    </note><w>čʼaǧačʼaj</w><gloss><q>шпулька</q></gloss></mentioned>
                [<bibl><author>С. Макалатия</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хеви, стр. 88 (на груз.
                яз.)</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Khevi, p. 88 (in
            Georgian)</biblScope></bibl>].</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">There is a doubtless connection with <mentioned xml:lang=""
                ><lang/><w>čʼäǧišk</w><gloss><q>locking bar</q></gloss></mentioned> and a probable
        connection with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><lang/><w>səǧəs</w><gloss><q>wedge</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>IV 620</biblScope></bibl>). If we assume that there
        was an original change pattern %iǧ%i || %iv%i (cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cigon"/>
        and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ciwan"/> ‘cast iron’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_suǧaq"
        /> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sovaq"/> ‘saiga’ etc.), then we can reconstruct a
        parallel form *%icavac%i which would be quite close to <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">()
                </note><w>цывца</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><w>цевка</w><gloss><q>bobbin</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The following word
            <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="">()
            </note><w>čʼaǧačʼaj</w><gloss><q>шпулька</q></gloss></mentioned> [<bibl><author>S.
                Makalatia.</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Хеви, стр. 88 (на груз.
                яз.)</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Khevi, p. 88 (in
            Georgian)</biblScope></bibl>] relates to the Ossetic %icʼæǧæʒ%i.</etym>
</entry>
